	<section1 id="np"><secTitle>Nominal Phrases</secTitle>
	<p>Nominal phrases can be very complex.  This section concentrates on those with common nouns as the lexical head.  Modification by articles, demonstratives, possessors, quantifiers and degree words, adjective phrases, pre/post-positional phrases and noun compounds is considered.   Nominal phrases headed by proper names are handled in section <sectionRef sec="prop"/> and those headed by pronouns, demonstratives, and quantifiers are handled in section <sectionRef sec="pn"/>.  Relative clauses are covered in section <sectionRef sec="relcl"/>.</p>
